Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: WhatsCrackin, LLC (the “Company”) was formed as a limited liability company in California under the name Convenient Concepts, LLC on February 11, 2015. On May 13, 2015, it changed its name to WhatsCrackin, LLC. The Company provides a proactive solution for nightlife venues that the Company believes can improve their current business operations through the use of the WhatsCrackin Mobile Application (the “App”). The venues which subscribe to their App are referred to “Venue Clients,” and the customers of the venues which use their App are referred to as “Users.”    Their principal product is the App, which enables Users who subscribe to their App to access exclusive deals, happy hour times, hours of operations, directions, and other information for nightlife venues in their areas who are also their Venue Clients. They are also in the process of developing the Geo-Chat (the “Geo-Chat”) technology, for which they plan to file the patent in the fourth quarter of 2016. They believe that the Geo-Chat will enable nightlife venue owners and managers to receive comments and opinions of their customers in real time when their customers are present at their venues.     They have developed a mobile application called the WhatsCrackin App. The App is an innovative tool that, once the Geo-Chat feature is implemented, they believe can provide their Venue Clients real-time comments from their customers.  The App is catered to the needs of Users who seek to frequent nightlife venues in their locality. Whether they are seeking a low-key type of venue or high-end dance club, the App will identify these preferences and give the user real-time information of what is happening in their local area.   Unlike other methods of receiving customer feedback, once the Geo-Chat feature is available, the App will be able to give their Venue Clients real-time feedback of what is happening in their location so that they can either remedy or enhance their customers’ experience based on the feedback received from the App.

Description: Strayer Education, Inc. (Nasdaq: STRA) is an education services holding company that owns Strayer University.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Strayer Education, Inc. (Nasdaq: STRA) is an education services holding company that owns Strayer University. The mission of Strayer University is simple: to make higher education achievable for working adults.  Strayer Education believes their value as a business is inherently linked to Strayer University's ability to deliver a high quality academic experience to students. Strayer Education's goal is to sustain and grow their business by offering rigorous and relevant academics that provide real returns to adult students, alumni and their employers.  As an open access institution, Strayer University makes educational attainment logistically simple. Students have the opportunity to take classes on campus, online or a combination of both. Each year, thousands of students who have made the commitment to educational attainment graduate from Strayer University and go on to become leaders in their organizations and communities.  Strayer Education, Inc., traces its roots to the founding of a small business college in 1892. That year, Dr. S. Irving Strayer opened the doors of Strayer's Business College in Baltimore, Md., to provide professional education to working adults.  For more than 123 years, the institution has stayed true to its original mission. In 1969, the school received licensure to grant Bachelor of Science degrees and was renamed Strayer College. Authorization to grant the Master of Science degree followed in 1987.  In 1996, Strayer Education, Inc., was established to raise capital for expansion and take Strayer College public. In 1998, Strayer College was granted university status and became Strayer University. In 2000, Strayer Education, Inc., successfully completed a major recapitalization. This included the introduction of a new senior management team led by Robert S. Silberman, current executive chairman of Strayer Education, Inc. In 2011, Strayer University acquired the Jack Welch Management Institute to offer an Executive MBA online.  Through the years Strayer University has maintained its commitment to academic quality and student success. Today the University takes great pride in its campus based and online degree programs and in the professional success of its alumni. Strayer Education continues to support Strayer University in fulfilling its mission of making education achievable for working adults.

Arrhythmias are abnormal electrical heart rhythms that adversely affect the mechanical activities of the heart and can potentially be fatal. The Company is developing microcatheter systems designed to provide enhanced access to arrhythmia causing tissue, to diagnose the arrhythmia by locating its origin ("mapping") and to restore normal heart rhythms by isolating and destroying the arrhythmia causing sites ("ablation") using radiofrequency ("RF") energy.

It also provides SeqCap Epi, an enrichment system that includes a set of target enrichment tools for DNA methylation assessment at single-base resolution, as well as offers SeqCap Epi kits and reagents. Ferrari Energy has provided oil and gas leases to over 850 homeowners and held multiple lease signing events to accommodate the residents of Broomfield, Colorado.     Ferrari Energy took its name from its founder, Adam Ferrari. Adam is a native of Chicago and was formally educated in chemical and biomolecular engineering. He completed his degree at the University of Illinois at Urbana Champaign and finished at the top of his class, graduating magna cum laude. As a young professional, Adam worked in the operations and business sides of the energy industry. After gaining ten years of direct industry experience, he took his passion for the energy industry and launched Ferrari Energy.     Adam believes in philanthropy and supports Next Steps of Chicago, an organization dedicated to serving people suffering from varying degrees of paralysis. Under his leadership, Ferrari Energy also made multiple donations to other organizations in Chicago and Denver, including St Jude Children’s Hospital, Freedom Service Dogs, and Denver Rescue Mission.
